{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #12: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Let $A$ be an infinite set such that there are no distinct $a,b,c\\in A$ such that $a\\mid (b+c)$ and $b,c>a$. Is there such an $A$ with\\[\\liminf \\frac{\\lvert A\\cap\\{1,\\ldots,N\\}\\rvert}{N^{1/2}}>0?\\]Does there exist some absolute constant $c>0$ such that there are always infinitely many $N$ with\\[\\lvert A\\cap\\{1,\\ldots,N\\}\\rvert<N^{1-c}?\\]Is it true that\\[\\sum_{n\\in A}\\frac{1}{n}<\\infty?\\] Current best: Elsholtz and Planitzer \\cite{ElPl17} have constructed such an $A$ with\\[\\lvert A\\cap\\{1,\\ldots,N\\}\\rvert\\gg \\frac{N^{1/2}}{(\\log N)^{1/2}(\\log\\log N)^2(\\log\\log\\log N)^2}.\\]Schoen \\cite{Sc01} proved that if all elements in $A$ are pairwise coprime then\\[\\lvert A\\cap\\{1,\\ldots,N\\}\\rvert \\ll N^{2/3}\\]for infinitely many $N$. Prize: no. Tags: number theory.","id":"vf_c528d3c2d358350b","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"AI-contributions wiki claim — wiki: Partial result (Lean) (solutions to first part and second part).","id":"vf_f5a36e65d717bdc6","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos12.erdos_12.parts.i https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos12.erdos_12.parts.i.","id":"vf_f64f8f16c87c76f3","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[{"accepted":false,"banked":true,"claim":"Erdős #12: the good example (Erdos12.isGood_example). Kernel-clean Lean proof — axioms {propext, Classical.choice, Quot.sound}, no sorryAx — ported AlphaProof reference. Produced by the vela prover-in-the-loop foundry; verified by the Lean kernel.","claimed_status":"","classification":"importable_attempt","id":"vat_02273e8429509697","kind":"theorem","lifecycle":"banked","location":"current_commit","mathematical_scope":"partial","method_channel":"","method_families":["lean_kernel","alphaproof_port"],"named_obstructions":["full_three_pa